				\begin{document}$$Q_{LOO}^{2}$$\end{document} metric analyses the model’s performance by iteratively leaving out one data point at a time and evaluating how well the model predicts the left-out points. It is a reliable measure of model performance, particularly in small datasets, as it ensures that the analysis can generalize to unseen data. The calculated correlation coefficient (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
